{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6362","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6362/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6362/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/owncloud/core/issues/6362/events","html_url":"https://github.com/owncloud/core/issues/6362","id":24193039,"number":6362,"title":"dbal sets not null by default","user":{"login":"ogasser","id":2095178,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/762006c20c19462b0e4ad786135cd2da?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2f15c8c5ca94e3b5ddbdfb912fee4f49e0.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"762006c20c19462b0e4ad786135cd2da","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser","html_url":"https://github.com/ogasser","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ogasser/received_events","type":"user","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"open","assignee":null,"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2013-12-12t17:11:19z","updated_at":"2013-12-17t21:26:48z","closed_at":null,"pull_request":{"html_url":null,"diff_url":null,"patch_url":null},"body":"the [dbal api](http://www.doctrine-project.org/api/dbal/2.4/source-class-doctrine.dbal.schema.column.html#67) sets every database column to *not null* by default.\r\n\r\nthe following declaration\r\n```\r\n      <field> \r\n        <name>ttl</name> \r\n        <type>integer</type> \r\n        <unsigned>true</unsigned> \r\n        <length>4</length> \r\n      </field>\r\n```\r\nis translated into the following mysql column:\r\n```ttl int(10) unsigned not null```\r\n\r\nwhen columns are created they should not have this behaviour by default. the sql standard specifies that the *not null* keyword enforces a constraint and no constraint should be there by default.\r\n\r\n","closed_by":null}